Hospitalizations - 2009 Scenarios

Pragati Prasad

2020-12-17

Mean, Cumulative with 95% CI, and Averted per 100K

Scenario RL01

Base scenario: no intervention

path <- "../model-forecasts/"

team.folder <- c("Columbia/COL/RL/", "Northeastern/RL/", "UTAustin/", "UVirginia/", "Imperial/", "Columbia/COL2/RL/", "Northeastern/RL2/", "Northeastern/RL3/")
team.abbrev <- c("COL", "NEU", "UTA", "UVA", "IMP", "COL2", "NEU", "NEU")
file.types <-c("SymIllness", "Hosp", "Deaths", "AntiviralTX")
scn = "RL01_"
read_overall_mean <- function(scn){
  
  cols <- c("sm.mean", "sm.perc2p5", "sm.perc97p5")

  s <- read.csv(paste0(path,team.folder[1],scn,file.types[2],"_",team.abbrev[1],".csv"))
  hosp <- data.frame(c(s[which(s$Agegroup == "Overall" &
                                       s$Bin %in% cols),],
                             `team` = team.abbrev[1]))
  
  for(i in 2:8){
    
    if(i == 4){
      scn = gsub("RL", "RL_", scn)
    }
    if(i == 5){
      scn = gsub("_", "", scn)
    }
    if(i == 6){
      scn = paste0(scn, "_")
    }
    
    f =  paste0(path,team.folder[i],scn,file.types[2],"_",team.abbrev[i],".csv")
    if(i == 5){
      f =  paste0(path,team.folder[i],scn,file.types[2],team.abbrev[i],".csv")
    }

    if(file.exists(f)){
      s <- read.csv(f)
      if(ncol(s) > 58){
        s <- s[-1]
      }
      if(i == 7){
        team.abbrev[i] = "NEU2"
      }
      if(i == 8){
        team.abbrev[i] = "NEU3"
      }
      hosp <- rbind.fill(hosp, data.frame(c(s[which(s$Agegroup == "Overall" & 
                                                      s$Bin %in% cols),],`team` = team.abbrev[i])))
    }
    
  }
  weeks <- paste0("Week",1:52)
  hosp$Cml[which(is.na(hosp$Cml))] <- hosp$cml[which(is.na(hosp$Cml))]
  cml <<- hosp[c("Cml", "team", "Bin")]
  
  long <- gather(hosp, week, illnesses, weeks, factor_key=TRUE)
  long$week <- as.integer(gsub("Week", "", long$week))
  
  cols <- c("Bin", "team", "week", "illnesses")
  long <- long[cols]
  long_wide <- spread(long, Bin, illnesses)
  
  return(long_wide)
}

long_RL01 <- read_overall_mean(scn = "RL01_")

ggplot(data = long_RL01, aes(x = week, y = sm.mean, group = team)) +
  geom_line(aes(color = team), lwd = 1.0) +
  geom_ribbon(aes(ymin = sm.perc2p5, ymax = sm.perc97p5, fill = team), alpha = 0.3,
              show.legend = FALSE)+
  ylab("Hospitalizations per 100,000") +
  scale_color_nejm() +
  scale_fill_nejm()

table <- cml[which(cml$Bin == "sm.mean"),]
table <- table[,-3]

table$lower <-  cml$Cml[which(cml$Bin == "sm.perc2p5")]
table$upper <-  cml$Cml[which(cml$Bin == "sm.perc97p5")]
table$Team <- table$team
table$`Cum. Hospitalizations per 100K` <- table$Cml
table$`95% CI` <- paste0("(", round(table$lower, 2), ", ", round(table$upper, 2), ")")

rownames(table) <- NULL

knitr::kable(table[5:7], digits = 2, caption = "RL01: 2009, no intervention", align=rep('c', 3)) %>%
  kable_styling(bootstrap_options = c("striped", "hover"))

#Bar chart for ages
team.folder <- c("Columbia/COL/RL/", "Northeastern/RL/", "UTAustin/", "UVirginia/", "Imperial/", "Columbia/COL2/RL/", "Northeastern/RL2/", "Northeastern/RL3/")
team.abbrev <- c("COL", "NEU", "UTA", "UVA", "IMP", "COL2", "NEU", "NEU")
file.types <-c("SymIllness", "Hosp", "Deaths", "AntiviralTX")
scn = "RL01_"
read_ages <- function(scn){
  
  cols <- c("sm.mean", "sm.perc2p5", "sm.perc97p5")

  s <- read.csv(paste0(path,team.folder[1],scn,file.types[2],"_",team.abbrev[1],".csv"))
  hosp <- data.frame(c(s[which(s$Agegroup != "Overall" &
                                       s$Bin %in% cols),],
                             `team` = team.abbrev[1]))
  
  for(i in 2:8){
    
    if(i == 4){
      scn = gsub("RL", "RL_", scn)
    }
    if(i == 5){
      scn = gsub("_", "", scn)
    }
    if(i == 6){
      scn = paste0(scn, "_")
    }
    
    f =  paste0(path,team.folder[i],scn,file.types[2],"_",team.abbrev[i],".csv")
    if(i == 5){
      f =  paste0(path,team.folder[i],scn,file.types[2],team.abbrev[i],".csv")
    }

    if(file.exists(f)){
      s <- read.csv(f)
      if(ncol(s) > 58){
        s <- s[-1]
      }
      if(i == 7){
        team.abbrev[i] = "NEU2"
      }
      if(i == 8){
        team.abbrev[i] = "NEU3"
      }
      hosp <- rbind.fill(hosp, data.frame(c(s[which(s$Agegroup != "Overall" & 
                                                      s$Bin %in% cols),],`team` = team.abbrev[i])))
    }
    
  }
  weeks <- paste0("Week",1:52)
  hosp$Cml[which(is.na(hosp$Cml))] <- hosp$cml[which(is.na(hosp$Cml))]
  cml <- hosp[c("Cml", "team", "Bin", "Agegroup")]
  cml$Agegroup <- sub("yr", "years", cml$Agegroup)
  cml$Agegroup <- factor(x = cml$Agegroup, levels = c("0-4 years", "5-17 years", "18-49 years", "50-64 years", "65+ years"))
  
  return(cml)
}

ages_1 <- read_ages(scn = "RL01_")
ggplot(ages_1, aes(fill=Agegroup, y=Cml, x=team)) + 
  geom_bar(position="fill", stat="identity") +
  ylab("Percent")+
  scale_fill_d3()

scenario = "RL01_"
averted_age <- data.frame(scenario = scenario,
                          team = ages_1$team[which(ages_1$Bin == "sm.mean")],
                          agegroup = ages_1$Agegroup[which(ages_1$Bin == "sm.mean")],
                          cml = ages_1$Cml[which(ages_1$Bin == "sm.mean")], 
                          lower = ages_1$Cml[which(ages_1$Bin == "sm.perc2p5")],
                          upper = ages_1$Cml[which(ages_1$Bin == "sm.perc97p5")])
write.csv(averted_age, "Hospitalizations_2009_RL01.csv")

table <- cml[which(cml$Bin == "sm.mean"),]
table <- table[,-3]

table$lower <-  cml$Cml[which(cml$Bin == "sm.perc2p5")]
table$upper <-  cml$Cml[which(cml$Bin == "sm.perc97p5")]
table$Team <- table$team
table$`Cum. Hospitalizations per 100K` <- table$Cml
table$`95% CI` <- paste0("(", round(table$lower, 2), ", ", round(table$upper, 2), ")")

table$`Averted Hospitalizations per 100K (RL01)` <- ifelse(table$Team %in% table1$Team, table1$`Cum. Hospitalizations per 100K` - table$`Cum. Hospitalizations per 100K`, NA)
table$`% Reduction in Burden (RL01)` <- ifelse(table$Team %in% table1$Team, 100 * (table1$`Cum. Hospitalizations per 100K` - table$`Cum. Hospitalizations per 100K`) / table1$`Cum. Hospitalizations per 100K`, NA)

rownames(table) <- NULL

knitr::kable(table[5:9], digits = 2, caption = "RL02: Vaccine, Compared to RL01", align=rep('c', 4)) %>%
  kable_styling(bootstrap_options = c("striped", "hover"))

table$lower <-  cml$Cml[which(cml$Bin == "sm.perc2p5")]
table$upper <-  cml$Cml[which(cml$Bin == "sm.perc97p5")]
table$Team <- table$team
table$`Cum. Hospitalizations per 100K` <- table$Cml
table$`95% CI` <- paste0("(", round(table$lower, 2), ", ", round(table$upper, 2), ")")

table$`Averted Hospitalizations per 100K (RL01)` <- ifelse(table$Team %in% table1$Team, table1$`Cum. Hospitalizations per 100K` - table$`Cum. Hospitalizations per 100K`, NA)
table$`% Reduction in Burden (RL01)` <- ifelse(table$Team %in% table1$Team, 100 * (table1$`Cum. Hospitalizations per 100K` - table$`Cum. Hospitalizations per 100K`) / table1$`Cum. Hospitalizations per 100K`, NA)

rownames(table) <- NULL

knitr::kable(table[5:9], digits = 2, caption = "RL07: Vaccine, Antivirals, and School Closure > 1%, Compared to RL01", align=rep('c', 4)) %>%
  kable_styling(bootstrap_options = c("striped", "hover"))
